label: Delilah's Pets Storefront
description: Storefront of Delilah's Pets Shop, a pet store that many are calling an accidental casualty of Ordinance 21-45's pet selling ban.

label: Puppies in Cages
description: Puppies in cramped metal cages; these puppies come from puppy mills, the kinds of organizations that Ordinance 21-45 is attempting to stop.

label: Puppies in Fence
description: Puppies behind a cramped fence; another example of puppy mill puppies in horrid conditions that Ordinance 21-45 puts a stop to.

label: Pets at Anthony's
description: Young dogs at Anthony's Pet Shop with no space; these are the kinds of poor conditions that Ordinance 21-45 aims to eliminate.

label: Dogs at Delilah's
description: Healthy dogs being sold at Delilah's; these healthy living conditions are an unintended casualty of Ordinance 21-45.

label: Dogs at Anthony's
description: Malnourished puppy at Anthony's; while the storefront is shut down, Anthony's is still selling dogs via Facebook.

label: Anthony's Storefront--Open
description: Anthony's Pet Shop as it is being constructed as a new pet store.

label: Anthony's Storefront--Closed
description: Anthony's Pet Shop months after it is closed, a sign advertising new shop space in front. No pets will ever be sold out of it ever again.

label: Bloomington City Hall
description: Bloomington City Hall. The city council recently passed Ordinance 21-45 unanimously.
